Source: https://github.com/supabase/supabase/blob/master/apps/docs/content/guides/ai/rag-with-permissions.mdx

This SQL command sets a custom session variable, `app.current_user_id`, to the ID of the current user. This variable is essential for Row-Level Security policies that rely on `current_setting()` to identify the user and filter data based on their permissions. Remember to replace '<current-user-id>' with the actual user's ID.

