### Configure Session-Level Auditing in PostgreSQL with PGAudit

Source: https://github.com/supabase/supabase/blob/master/apps/docs/content/guides/database/extensions/pgaudit.mdx

Demonstrates how to check and set PGAudit logging within a database session (e.g., psql connection). By default, PGAudit logs nothing until configured. The session-specific settings allow temporary audit configurations that only apply to the current connection.

```sql
-- returns 'none'
show pgaudit.log;
```

```sql
-- log CREATE, ALTER, and DROP events
set pgaudit.log = 'ddl';

-- log all CREATE, ALTER, DROP, and SELECT events
set pgaudit.log = 'read, ddl';

-- log nothing
set pgaudit.log = 'none';
```
